				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Don't charm Eldrig<a name="28935"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 1:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you are lucky enough to find Eldrig near the Burning Woods zone line, then by all means try and charm him and have him follow you down the &quot;alley&quot; leading to BW. 
<br />

<br />
Break Charm
<br />
Hit him with Largo's, take a small beating
<br />
Hit him with Song of Midnight
<br />
Tank heavily and lay a Cold/Poison/Disease Chant on him
<br />
keep twisting Snare, Fear, DoT and Tank
<br />

<br />
This may take a little while, but once you get it down, summoning is not an issue. Plus he won't poof if feared and snared and you're facing his backside within melee range.
<br />

<br />
If you're lucky, you'll get him single. I happened to get him with an add and had to zone out, then back in to get him where I wanted him. I also had a bud help me, but this is the solo tactic I'd use.
<br />

<br />
Wila...
<br />
</span></td>
